content:
The `staking-deposit-cli` creates keystores with version=4, like
```
{
    "crypto": {
        "kdf": {
            ...
        },
        "checksum": {
            ...
        },
        "cipher": {
            ...
        }
    },
    "description": "",
    "pubkey": "b710b415137954ce322368210e4c3de039ec655c652c4af9ad7d1eec2eeb03cfcfa3c2903d8c30abefcc7722d4d34619",
    "path": "m/12381/3600/0/0/0",
    "uuid": "09e7d714-43cc-4376-be38-a0bb9bcb628f",
    "version": 4
}
```
However I've only seen documentations up to version 3 (for eg. this seems to be the official docs? https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Web3-Secret-Storage-Definition)

geth only has `DecryptDataV3` (https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/accounts/keystore#DecryptDataV3). Is it because V3 is for ECDSA and V4 is only for BLS signatures? Is this documented anywhere..?
